Citation.sTitle: Static Dielectric Permittivity and Electric Conductivity of N-Methylacetamide + N,N-Dimethylacetamide Mixtures
Citation.sAbstract: Impedance spectroscopy (IS) was used for the determination of the static dielectric permittivity and the  electric conductivity of N-methylacetamide (NMA) + N,N-dimethylacetamide (DMA) mixtures over the  whole concentration range and over the temperature range of 303.15 K to 393.15 K. The static permittivity  values obtained with IS for both neat compounds at different temperatures are in a very good agreement  with those measured with the classical dielectric methods. In NMA + DMA mixtures, the permittivity  deviations (Aa) from the concentration additive rule are strongly negative, and the Aa dependence on the  mole fraction of NMA was fitted to the Redlich-Kister equation.
